ed%20Abu%20Shaban%20often%20gets%20up%20at%203%3A00%20am%20in%20Toronto%20to%20remotely%20teach%20his%20students%20in%20Gaza%20--%20motivated%20by%20loyalty%20to%20his%20trapped%20pupils%2C%20and%20a%20deep%20sense%20of%20guilt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShaban%2C%20an%20academic%20who%20fled%20Gaza%20days%20after%20October%207%2C%202023%2C%20said%20he%20has%20an%20obligation%20to%20students%20in%20the%20Palestinian%20Territory%20desperate%20to%20study%20in%20defiance%20of%20unimaginable%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20said%20he%20has%20a%20responsibility%20to%20help%20preserve%20higher%20education%20in%20Gaza%2C%20while%20the%20world%20is%20focused%20on%20the%20humanitarian%20emergency.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%2050-year-old%20conceded%20that%20guilt%20also%20weighs%20on%20him.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGuilty%20for%20leaving%20Gaza%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20AFP.%20%26quot%3BLike%20we%20just%20abandoned%20our%20country%2C%20our%20people%2C%20our%20institution.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShaban%20is%20still%20the%20dean%20of%20the%20Faculty%20of%20Agriculture%20and%20Veterinary%20Medicine%20at%20Al-Azhar%20University%2C%20which%20was%20destroyed%20--%20along%20with%20most%20university%20buildings%20--%20by%20Israeli%20air%20strikes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShaban%20crossed%20to%20Egypt%20shortly%20after%20the%20war%20began%2C%20anticipating%20Israel's%20response%20to%20the%20Hamas%20attack%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bmassive%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECanadian%20contacts%20arranged%20a%20posting%20at%20Toronto's%20York%20University%2C%20where%20he%20is%20a%20visiting%20professor%20in%20the%20Faculty%20of%20Environmental%20and%20Urban%20Change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20campus%20office%20with%20empty%20book%20shelves%20and%20mostly%20bare%20walls%2C%20Shaban%20explained%20that%20he%20felt%20compelled%20to%20help%20make%20Al-Azhar%20operational%20in%20some%20form.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20wanted%20%26quot%3Bto%20give%20the%20very%20clear%20message%20for%20the%20whole%20world%3A%20Yes%2C%20they%20just%20destroyed%20our%20infrastructure.%20Yes%2C%20they%20destroyed%20our%20buildings...%20but%20we%20are%20still%20alive%20and%20we%20will%20just%20continue%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20actually%20a%20responsibility%20for%20our%20students%2C%20for%20our%20nation%2C%20and%20for%20our%20independent%20state%20in%20the%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E-%20Hunger%20to%20study%20-%3Cbr%3E%5CnShaban%2C%20who%20is%20on%20Al-Azhar's%20board%2C%20said%20its%20pre-war%20enrolment%20was%2014%2C000%20students.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20registration%20opened%20for%20online%20courses%20earlier%20this%20year%20he%20expected%201%2C000%20students%20to%20join.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20got%2010%2C000%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20really%2C%20for%20me%2C%20shocking%20because%2C%20just%20imagine%3A%20you%20live%20in%20a%20tent%2C%20you%20have%20no%20electricity%2C%20you%20have%20no%20internet.%20You%20have%20nothing%20at%20all.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20you%20still%20have%20the%20hope%20to%20go%20to%20sign%20up%20for%20online%20courses%20and%20to%20walk%20for%20five%20(kilometres)%20to%20get%20internet%20connection%20and%20even%20to%20communicate%2C%20to%20sit%20and%20study.%20And%20sometimes%20you%20risk%20your%20life%20even%20while%20you%20are%20searching%20for%20internet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShaban%20conceded%20his%20personal%20schedule%20is%20%26quot%3Bstressful%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20he%20tries%20to%20work%20in%20two%20time%20zones.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20day%20last%20month%2C%20he%20was%20up%20at%203%3A00%20am%20to%20join%20a%20workshop%20on%20Gaza's%20food%20system%2C%20before%20an%20Al-Azhar%20board%20meeting%20at%206%3A00%20am.%20He%20then%20headed%20to%20his%20Toronto%20office%20to%20prepare%20a%20guest%20lecture%20on%20the%20Gaza%20war.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20evenings%20and%20weekends%20he%20records%20and%20uploads%20lectures%20for%20his%20Palestinian%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShaban%20said%20the%20study%20program%20is%20flexible%2C%20given%20the%20challenges%20of%20internet%20access.%20Students%20watch%20lectures%20and%20complete%20assigments%20when%20they%20can%20get%20online.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E-%20Star%20student%20killed%20-%3Cbr%3E%5CnHe%20said%20students%20in%20Gaza%20can%20be%20%26quot%3Bangry%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bpushy%26quot%3B%3A%20they%20want%20to%20know%2C%20for%20example%2C%20when%20they%20will%20able%20to%20do%20lab%20work%2C%20even%20though%20all%20the%20labs%20have%20been%20destroyed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShaban%20said%20he%20understands%20their%20frustrations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%20you%20feel%20the%20students%20are%20looking%20at%20us%20like%20we%20can%20do%20things%20that%20actually%20are%20not%20doable%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20to%20be%20responsive%20in%20a%20gentle%20way.%26quot%3B%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20agitated%20student%20messages%20pour%20in%2C%20Shaban%20said%20he%20reminds%20himself%20that%20he%20is%20living%20comfortably%20in%20a%20city%20with%20electricity%20and%20grocery%20stores%20stocked%20with%20food.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B(I)%20try%20just%20to%20provide%20them%20with%20whatever%20support%20that%20I%20can.%20There%20are%20many%20things%20that%20I%20cannot%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStudents%20who%20have%20died%20are%20always%20front%20of%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20recalled%20five%20engineering%20students%20killed%20as%20they%20gathered%20by%20an%20internet%20source%20to%20work%20on%20an%20assignment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShaban%20said%20he%20will%20never%20forget%20his%20%26quot%3Bstar%20student%26quot%3B%20Bilal%20al%20Aish%2C%20who%2C%20days%20before%20the%20war%20started%2C%20was%20trying%20to%20decide%20whether%20to%20pursue%20a%