guided%20rockets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHanwha%20Group%20rose%20from%2042nd%20place%20in%20the%20world%20in%202022%20to%2024th%20in%202023.%20It%20brought%20in%20%245.71%20billion%20in%20arms%20revenue%20in%202023%2C%20up%2052.7%25%20from%20%243.74%20billion%20in%202022%2C%20per%20SIPRI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20K239%20Chunmoo%20rocket%20artillery%20system%20of%20the%20South%20Korean%20military%20is%20on%20display%20at%20the%20Eurosatory%20Defense%20and%20Security%20expo.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675131d18fbb2783ed2fd721%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222947%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHanwha%20has%20been%20selling%20weapons%20like%20the%20K239%20Chunmoo%20rocket%20artillery%20system%20to%20European%20countries.%20Poland%20placed%20a%20billion-dollar%20order%20for%20the%20MLRS%20this%20year.%3Cp%3EArtur%20Widak%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20SIPRI%2C%20much%20of%20the%20Seoul-based%20conglomerate's%20arms%20revenue%20was%20driven%20by%20its%202023%20acquisition%20of%20one%20of%20South%20Korea's%20three%20biggest%20shipbuilders%2C%20DSME.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFive%20Japanese%20firms%20were%20listed%20among%20the%20world's%20top%20100%20defense%20firms.%20They%20include%20Mitsubishi%20Heavy%20Industries%2C%20which%20saw%20a%2023.9%25%20increase%20in%20arms%20revenue%20to%20%243.89%20billion%20in%202023%2C%20and%20Fujitsu%2C%20which%20saw%20a%2016.4%25%20increase%20to%20%241.85%20billion%20that%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELiang%20said%20Japan's%20defense%20industry%20has%20benefited%20from%20a%20major%20increase%20in%20Tokyo's%20military%20spending%20policy.%20%26quot%3BDomestic%20orders%20for%20advanced%20systems%20have%20soared%2C%20further%20driving%20revenue%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMitsubishi%20Heavy%20Industries%2C%20for%20example%2C%20builds%20submarines%20and%20aircraft%20for%20Jap